                ğŸ”„ Authorization Flow per Case
                
Auth Flow per Scenario
â”œâ”€â”€ Inbound (External â†’ Salesforce)
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ Use OAuth 2.0 â†’ Salesforce issues access token
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ External system includes token in requests
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ Salesforce validates scope + token â†’ processes API call
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ If using Named Credentials: Salesforce manages token refresh

â”œâ”€â”€ Outbound (Salesforce â†’ External)
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ Use Named Credentials
â”‚   â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ Configure Auth flow (OAuth or Basic)
â”‚   â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ Store client secret securely
â”‚   â”‚   â””â”€â”€ Token automatically added to HTTP request
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ Manual Auth in Apex
â”‚   â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ Manually set `Authorization` header
â”‚   â”‚   â””â”€â”€ Manage token lifecycle yourself
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ Platform Events or CDC â†’ Middleware (e.g., Mulesoft)
â”‚   â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ No direct auth in Salesforce
â”‚   â”‚   â””â”€â”€ Middleware handles auth to downstream system
